    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-06-02T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-06-02T15:00:00-05:00" n="357"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_PPS1">PPS</gloss> Files, Lot 64–D 563</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minutes of the Policy Planning Staff, Wednesday, June 2, 1948,
                        4 p. m. to 5 p. m.</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        from="1948-06-02T16:00:00-04:00" to="1948-06-02T17:00:00-04:00">June 2,
                        1948, 4 p.m. to 5 p.m.</date>
                </dateline>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <table cols="3" rows="11">
                    <row>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">Present:</cell>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">George Butler</cell>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">Carlton Savage</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">Bernard Gufler</cell>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">Henry Villard<note n="1" xml:id="d357fn1">Messrs.
                                Butler, Gufler, and Villard were members of the Policy Planning
                                Staff; Mr. Savage, who drafted these minutes, was the Staff’s
                                Executive Secretary.</note>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">Willard L. Thorp, <gloss target="#t_E1">E</gloss>
                        </cell>
                        <cell/>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">Loy W. Henderson, <gloss target="#t_NEA1"
                                >NEA</gloss>
                        </cell>
                        <cell/>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">John D. Hickerson, <gloss target="#t_EUR1"
                                >EUR</gloss>
                        </cell>
                        <cell/>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">Carlisle H. Humelsine, <gloss target="#t_SS1"
                                >S/S</gloss>
                        </cell>
                        <cell/>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">Samuel K. C. Kopper, <gloss target="#t_NEA1"
                                >NEA</gloss>
                        </cell>
                        <cell/>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">Robert M. McClintock, <gloss target="#t_UNA1"
                                >UNA</gloss>
                        </cell>
                        <cell/>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">Gordon P. Merriam, <gloss target="#t_NE1"
                                >NE</gloss>
                        </cell>
                        <cell/>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">Durward V. Sandifer, <gloss target="#t_UNA1"
                                >UNA</gloss>
                        </cell>
                        <cell/>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell rendition="#hanging">Fraser Wilkins, <gloss target="#t_NE1">NE</gloss>
                        </cell>
                        <cell/>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p>There was a discussion of the question of placing the Palestine problem before
                    the National Security Council, in accordance with the <pb facs="0578" n="1088"
                        xml:id="pg_1088"/> Policy Planning Staff recommendation, approved by the
                    Secretary and Mr. Lovett, that the course which this Government pursues with
                    respect to Palestine should be cleared with the National Security Council. It
                    was agreed that we should begin immediately to develop a paper on Palestine and
                    its overall policy implications, particularly with respect to the Middle East,
                    for submission to the Secretary and Mr. Lovett and eventual clearance through
                    the National Security Council.</p>
            </div>
